data.title: Why did CBS decide to switch eight of its owned stations from The CW to independent status?
data.meta_description: Answer: Paramount Global, owner of the CBS network and the CBS Stations Group, sold all but a small share of its ownership of the CW (Paramount owned one half and Discovery WB owned the other half) to Nexstar Media Group, which owns a large number of TV stations.
